430758I stayed briefly in San Francisco and the room was located very well, but very basic with its own bathroom. There is a good deal of street traffic/noise and the white blinds create quite a luminous morning, it was not dark at all. There is no air conditioning and the sun hits that side of the building, so in the afternoon it is a bit warm. The room has a high ceiling and a decent floor. There is a noisy fridge, but they all seem to be. This room is really a budget/value type of room, really designed for a hard boiled experienced Airbnb urban traveler. You have to manipulate no less than two lock mechanisms in lower lighting (one somewhat sophisticated) and walk up narrow steep stairs. As this listing is most likely run by a business type of Airbnb host you have to be dexterous and patient with the process as you will most likely not meet the host in person, which I actually feel is unfortunate due to the busy area, lockbox, unique electronic lock and their underlying procedures. Alice was very communicable and replies quickly during the day. There was a key issue, but later was ironed out in a positive manner. The older building is a bit old as many are in the area. There are many people coming, going, whom possibly live there, some may even be in transitional housing and others appear to be young techie/student travelers. There is a great artesian style bar across the street, but also some homeless in the area, so be vigilant. If you are looking for basic bed no frills, a superb location, and a value price then this is ideal.2019-09-095269707733810736127753648Michael
